---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Robots Move!"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={2}
  phase="Phase 1: Unplugged"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="🚶"
  objective="Explore how robots move their body parts"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Your child will explore different types of movement (arms, head, wheels) and understand that robots can only move in ways they are built for.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Open floor space</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Masking tape (to mark "robot zones")</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Optional: toy cars, spinning tops, wind-up toys</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Movement Warm-Up (5 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Play "robot freeze dance." Move like a stiff robot when music plays, freeze when it stops. Encourage jerky, mechanical movements.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Body Parts Game (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Tape labels on body parts: ARM, HEAD, WAIST, LEGS. Shout a body part and how to move it: "ARM — up!" "HEAD — left!" Practice together. Talk: which body parts can Reachy Mini move? (arms, head, eyes)</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Make a Movement Recipe (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Together, create a "movement recipe" — a list of 4 moves to make a silly robot routine. Write or draw each step. Perform it 3 times getting more robot-like each time!</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Cool-Down (5 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Look at a picture of Reachy Mini together. Point at each part. Ask: "What do you think THIS part does?"</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What's harder — moving like a robot or moving like a person? Why?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Can robots dance? What would that look like?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 Keep movements BIG and exaggerated — small children love physicality. The goal is motor play + concept introduction.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">💡 Your "movement recipe" is actually introducing the concept of an algorithm — don't use the word, just build the intuition!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
